# Shopify + Next.js Admin Rules (2026)

## API surface
- **Storefront API** is the public, customer-facing GraphQL surface
  (`src/lib/shopify/client.ts` → `shopifyFetch`). Use it for everything
  under the `(site)` route group, the cart, and the search page.
- **Admin API** is the private back-office GraphQL surface
  (`src/lib/shopify-admin.ts` → `shopifyAdminFetch`). Use it ONLY inside
  the `(admin)` route group, inside `/api` route handlers, or inside
  server actions invoked by admin pages.
- Never import `shopify-admin.ts`, `admin-data.ts`, `admin-session.ts`,
  `admin-queries.ts`, or anything under `src/app/(admin)/` from a Client
  Component. They carry the `server-only` marker.

## Environment variables
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` is shipped to the browser. NEVER prefix Admin API
  variables with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` — specifically `SHOPIFY_ADMIN_API_ACCESS_TOKEN`,
  `SHOPIFY_ADMIN_API_VERSION`, `ADMIN_PANEL_PASSWORD`, `ADMIN_SESSION_SECRET`,
  and `SHOPIFY_REVALIDATION_SECRET` must stay unprefixed.

## GraphQL
- Admin API version is pinned to `2026-04` via `SHOPIFY_ADMIN_API_VERSION`.
  When generating or modifying admin queries, assume that schema.
- Storefront API version is pinned via `SHOPIFY_STOREFRONT_API_VERSION`.
  Do not silently bump either version.
- When proposing new GraphQL, prefer reading the schema via the
  `@shopify/dev-mcp` MCP server (if configured) over guessing.
- Fragment names must be unique per document. When composing a query,
  include each fragment definition exactly once — use the `_BUNDLE`
  constants in `src/lib/shopify/queries/fragments.ts` for this.

## Mutations
- All Shopify mutations (product create/update, cart, orders) must run
  inside a Next.js Server Action or a route handler — never `fetch`'d
  from the browser.
- After a mutation, call `updateTag(…)` with every tag whose cache needs
  to be invalidated. Shared tags live on `TAGS` in
  `src/lib/shopify/normalizers.ts` and `src/lib/admin-data.ts`.
- Shopify returns `userErrors` (or `mediaUserErrors`, `orderUserErrors`,
  etc.) in the mutation payload. Always call `throwIfUserErrors(…)` on
  the payload before trusting the result.

## Images
- Product images use `next/image`. Allowed hosts are configured in
  `next.config.ts` under `images.remotePatterns`; both `cdn.shopify.com`
  and `{shop}.myshopify.com` are whitelisted.
- When adding a new external image source, update `remotePatterns`
  rather than disabling the Image optimizer.

## Routing
- `src/app/(site)/` holds storefront routes — wrapped by the site
  Header/Footer/CartDrawer.
- `src/app/(admin)/` holds admin routes — no site chrome. The
  `(admin)/admin/(shell)/` sub-group adds the sidebar; `admin/login`
  lives OUTSIDE that sub-group so the login page stays bare.
- `/admin/*` is protected by `src/middleware.ts` (JWT session cookie).
  Any new admin route is automatically protected because the matcher is
  `/admin/:path*`.

## React
- Client components must have `"use client"` on line 1.
- Avoid `useEffect` purely to derive state from props — use the
  "reset state on prop change" pattern or `useSyncExternalStore`.
- Never call impure functions (`Date.now()`, `Math.random()`) directly
  inside `useMemo`/render — snapshot them once in a `useState`
  initializer.
